  <front>
   <head>The INDOLENT.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">WHAT self-sufficiency and false content</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Benumb the senses of the indolent!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Dead to all purposes of good, or ill,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Alive alone in an</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His only vice in  lies,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And his sole virtue is his</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Business he deems too hard, trifles too easy,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And doing nothing finds himself too busy.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Silence he cannot bear, noise is distraction,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Noise kills with bustle, silence with reflection;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No want he feels, â€” what has he to pursue?</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To him 'tis less to  than to</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The  world's a fool, the  a sot,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And his sole hope to be by all forgot:</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Wealth is procur'd with toil, and kept with fear,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Knowledge by labour purchas'd costs too dear;</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Friendship's a clog, and family a jest,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A wife but a bad bargain at the best;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Honour a bubble, subject to a breath,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And all engagements vain since null'd by death;</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thus all the wise esteem, he can despise,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And  'tis he alone is wise:</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Yet, all his wish possessing, finds no rest,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="12">And only lives to know,</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
